result.text:
Ethel Cain tells Rolling Stone about signing a deal with Prescription Songs, which she did not know was owned by Dr. Luke at the time of signing:

“I just decided, ‘I’m here now and can’t really go anywhere for a while. So I’m just going to mind my business and make my music.’ But if I had my choice, I would much prefer to do business with somebody else. I’ll just say that… But yeah, if I could go back in time and do it differently, I probably wouldn’t put my name on that paper.”
